## Server vs Client Components

```
Server (no directive)  →  Box · VStack · HStack · Heading · Text · Card · Badge · Separator
Client ('use client')  →  Button (onClick) · Dialog · Drawer · Form · tabs with state · all hooks
```

---

## Forms

Always start with Pattern 1. Move down only when you need more control.

```tsx
'use client';
import { Form, FormFieldItem, FormFieldItems, FormRoot } from '@paalstack/react-ui';
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import { zodResolver } from '@hookform/resolvers/zod';
```

### Field types

| `type` | Renders |
|---|---|
| `'input'` | `<Input>` — use `inputType` for `'email'`, `'password'`, `'tel'` |
| `'textarea'` | `<Textarea>` |
| `'number'` | `<NumberInput>` — via `numberInputProps` |
| `'select'` | `<Select>` — pass `options: { label, value }[]` or `string[]` |
| `'combobox'` | Searchable `<Combobox>` — pass `options` |
| `'multi-select'` | `<MultiSelect>` — pass `options` |
| `'checkbox'` | Single `<Checkbox>` |
| `'checkbox-group'` | Group — pass `options: string[]` |
| `'radio-group'` | `<RadioGroup>` — pass `options: string[]` |
| `'date-picker'` | `<DatePicker>` |
| `'date-range-picker'` | `<DateRangePicker>` |
| `'input-group'` | `<InputGroup>` with `addonStart` / `addonEnd` |
| `'field'` | Custom in label+error shell — `render: ({ field }) => <Input {...field} />` |
| `'custom'` | Raw render — `render: ({ field }) => <YourComponent {...field} />` |

### Pattern 1 — `fields` prop (default)

```tsx
<Form
  form={form}
  onSubmit={handleSubmit}
  fields={[
    { type: 'input',    name: 'email',    label: 'Email',    inputType: 'email',    required: true },
    { type: 'input',    name: 'password', label: 'Password', inputType: 'password', required: true },
    { type: 'checkbox', name: 'terms',    label: 'I agree to the terms',            required: true },
  ]}
  hideResetButton
/>
```

### Pattern 2 — mixed `fields` + `FormFieldItem` children

```tsx
<Form form={form} onSubmit={handleSubmit} fields={[/* main fields */]} hideResetButton>
  <FormFieldItem control={form.control} field={{ type: 'checkbox', name: 'terms', label: 'Agree', required: true }} />
</Form>
```

### Pattern 3 — `fields={[]}` + grouped children

```tsx
<Form form={form} onSubmit={handleSubmit} fields={[]} submitText="Register">
  <Text className="text-sm font-semibold">Personal Info</Text>
  <Box className="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
    <FormFieldItems fields={personalFields} control={form.control} />
  </Box>
  <FormFieldItem control={form.control} field={{ type: 'checkbox', name: 'terms', label: 'Agree', required: true }} />
</Form>
```

### Pattern 4 — `FormRoot` (full custom escape hatch)

```tsx
<FormRoot {...form}>
  <Box as="form" onSubmit={form.handleSubmit(handleSubmit)} className="space-y-4">
    <FormFieldItem control={form.control} field={{ type: 'input', name: 'username', label: 'Username', required: true }} />
    <Button type="submit">Submit</Button>
  </Box>
</FormRoot>
```

### Button customisation

```tsx
// Custom submit via render prop
<Form form={form} onSubmit={handleSubmit} fields={fields}
  SubmitButton={({ isSubmitting, onFormSubmit }) => (
    <Button type="submit" onClick={onFormSubmit} isLoading={isSubmitting} className="w-full">
      {isSubmitting ? 'Saving...' : 'Save'}
    </Button>
  )}
/>

// Custom children buttons
<Form form={form} onSubmit={handleSubmit} fields={fields} hideSubmitButton hideResetButton>
  <Box className="flex gap-2 justify-end">
    <Button variant="outline" onClick={() => form.reset()}>Cancel</Button>
    <Button type="submit">Save</Button>
  </Box>
</Form>
```

